div.p:

   Deut. 30.10, 11, 12, 13, 14.Therefore my Dear Neighbours, I once more call unto you, to come unto that word, which Moses directed the Children of Israel unto; it is the same word the Apostle Paul directed the


Romans unto,
   Rom. 10 7, 8. and it is the same word that I am calling you to adhere unto, and if you are willing to come off from a Rebellious and a Disobedient life, if not, I testifie unto you that you are a Rebellious and a Disobedient People; if you will not come to hear the word of the Lord, or the Spirit of Christ, that is, checking or reproving you in your Consciences for evil Thoughts, Words, and Actions; I surely testifie unto you, that this word is as living and as powerful, as it was in the dayes of Moses and of Paul: It is the living word of Reconciliation that will reconcile unto God, if you will hear it and obey it;
   John 1.3, 4. it will raise you from the grave of Sin, to Righteousness of Life, to walk in the new Birth, of which you must be born again;
   John 3.3. if you will be inheriters of the Kingdom of Heaven, or if you have a desire to be the King of Heavens Sons and Daughters; you must walk in the straight and narrow way that leadeth to life everlasting. And surely there is but one Way, and one Door by which you must enter; all which is pure and Holy, for it is Chirst, for he is the Way, the Door, the Light and Life of every true Christian; for Man of himself is not able to do any thing that is good, but the Guide, the Help, and the Assistance of every true Christian, is and must be by the Power of Christs Spirit, Dwelling, Ruling, Raigning, and Governing in and over the Souls and Hearts of Mankind.
